Jarryd Hayne: Not only Aussie making headlines Young Australian punter Michael Dickson is making the news for all the wrong reasons after his performance seemingly cost his Texas team the game.
PT0M45S 620 349 He may have had less publicity than NRL star turned 49er Jarryd Hayne, but young Australian punter Michael Dickson is now making headlines in the US for all the wrong reasons.
It was the stuff of a sportsperson's nightmares. Dickson's big moment became a big embarrassment with less than two minutes to go in his game for Texas against Oklahoma state.
As Oklahoma tied the game, Texas, at fourth and one, were forced to punt.
The snap from Dickson's teammate was good. Dickson's hands, not too much.
Advertisement The Aussie fumbled the cleanest of passes, watching the ball tumble past his head, before running to recover it, only to then kick it out on the full behind the line of scrimmage.
Texas lost six yards as a result, allowing Oklahoma to kick for a 40-yard field goal with just six seconds on the clock, and thus steal the game 30-27.
Unfortunately, it was Texas' second loss in three games due to mistakes from special teams. The Longhorns were down seven points against Cal before scoring a 45-yard touchdown.
Then came the error.
The kick for the extra point, which would have tied the game, was so far right it never looked like scoring. With just over a minute left on the clock, Texas lost that game by a point.
